<subSubSection id="6AB59980FFF3FF93FF67FBBCAA5C3E1C" pageId="5" pageNumber="586" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="2210CA0BFFF3FF93FF67FBBCADFB3FAC" blockId="5.[151,1437,1034,2035]" pageId="5" pageNumber="586">
<emphasis id="10DB1619FFF3FF93FF67FBBCA8763F19" bold="true" box="[151,274,1034,1060]" pageId="5" pageNumber="586">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Males of 
<taxonomicName id="E5AFB188FFF3FF93FE71FBBDAB8C3F18" authority="Simon, 1903" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1903" box="[385,744,1035,1061]" class="Arachnida" family="Anyphaenidae" genus="Mesilla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="5" pageNumber="586" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vittiventris">
<emphasis id="10DB1619FFF3FF93FE71FBBDAB373F19" box="[385,595,1035,1061]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="586">Mesilla vittiventris</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="463EB7FAFFF3FF93FDAAFBBDAB8C3F18" author="Simon, E." box="[602,744,1035,1061]" pageId="5" pageNumber="586" pagination="21 - 39" refId="ref5673" refString="Simon, E. (1903) Descriptions d'arachnides nouveaux. Annales de la Societe Entomologique de Belgique, 47, 21 - 39. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. part. 25299" type="journal article" year="1903">Simon, 1903</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished by their very long, thin cymbium; a long median apophysis distally erected and single, extremely short retrolateral tibial apophysis (
<figureCitation id="BA94D68EFFF3FF93FB78FB99ADA93F74" box="[1160,1229,1071,1097]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1872,1896]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,272,1848]" captionTargetId="figure-68@6.[189,1398,272,1848]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3A-H. Mesilla vittiventris Simon, 1903. Male (ICN-Ar 9696):A habitus, dorsal view; C left palp, retroventral view; D palp, retrolateral view; E palp, ventral view; F leg I, ventral view. Female (ICN-Ar 6271): B habitus, dorsal view; G epigynum, ventral view; H epigynum, dorsal view.Abbreviations:A, atrium; CD, copulatory ducts; E, embolus; FD, fertilization ducts; LB, lateral borders; MA, median apophysis; RTA, retrolateral tibial apophysis; S, spermathecae; SD, spermatic ducts; SR, seminal receptacles; T, tegulum. Scale bars: A, B, F: 2mm; C: 1mm; D: 0.5mm; E–H: 0.2mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4506506" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4506506/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="586">Figs 3</figureCitation>
C–E). Females are characterized by the epigynum with long, wide lateral borders, curved inward and with a septum; a long atrium and small seminal receptacles situated on the anterior third of the copulatory ducts (
<figureCitation id="BA94D68EFFF3FF93FBE1FBC1ADF63FAC" box="[1041,1170,1143,1169]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1872,1896]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,272,1848]" captionTargetId="figure-68@6.[189,1398,272,1848]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3A-H. Mesilla vittiventris Simon, 1903. Male (ICN-Ar 9696):A habitus, dorsal view; C left palp, retroventral view; D palp, retrolateral view; E palp, ventral view; F leg I, ventral view. Female (ICN-Ar 6271): B habitus, dorsal view; G epigynum, ventral view; H epigynum, dorsal view.Abbreviations:A, atrium; CD, copulatory ducts; E, embolus; FD, fertilization ducts; LB, lateral borders; MA, median apophysis; RTA, retrolateral tibial apophysis; S, spermathecae; SD, spermatic ducts; SR, seminal receptacles; T, tegulum. Scale bars: A, B, F: 2mm; C: 1mm; D: 0.5mm; E–H: 0.2mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4506506" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4506506/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="586">Figs 3G, H</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2210CA0BFFF3FF93FF37FB2DAA5C3E1C" blockId="5.[151,1437,1034,2035]" pageId="5" pageNumber="586">
<emphasis id="10DB1619FFF3FF93FF37FB2DA8623F88" bold="true" box="[199,262,1179,1205]" pageId="5" pageNumber="586">Note.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="463EB7FAFFF3FF93FEFFFB2DA8A93F88" author="Brescovit, A. D." box="[271,461,1179,1205]" pageId="5" pageNumber="586" pagination="1 - 187" refId="ref5286" refString="Brescovit, A. D. (1997) Revisao de Anyphaeninae Bertkau a nivel de generos na regiao neotropical (Araneae, Anyphaenidae). Revista Brasileira de Zoologia, 13, 1 - 187. https: // doi. org / 10.1590 / S 0101 - 81751996000500001" type="journal article" year="1997">Brescovit (1997)</bibRefCitation>
illustrated the internal genitalia of the 
<taxonomicName id="E5AFB188FFF3FF93FC7AFB2DAD3B3F89" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1903" box="[906,1119,1179,1205]" class="Arachnida" family="Anyphaenidae" genus="Mesilla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="5" pageNumber="586" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vittiventris">
<emphasis id="10DB1619FFF3FF93FC7AFB2DAD3B3F89" box="[906,1119,1179,1205]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="586">Mesilla vittiventris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<typeStatus id="FD1474A9FFF3FF93FB97FB2DADF33F88" box="[1127,1175,1179,1205]" pageId="5" pageNumber="586">type</typeStatus>
specimen. That epigynum, being detached from the abdomen and suffering from dissection, did not present the copulatory ducts, only fertilization ducts (
<bibRefCitation id="463EB7FAFFF3FF93FE80FB55AB463FC0" author="Brescovit, A. D." box="[368,546,1251,1277]" pageId="5" pageNumber="586" pagination="1 - 187" refId="ref5286" refString="Brescovit, A. D. (1997) Revisao de Anyphaeninae Bertkau a nivel de generos na regiao neotropical (Araneae, Anyphaenidae). Revista Brasileira de Zoologia, 13, 1 - 187. https: // doi. org / 10.1590 / S 0101 - 81751996000500001" type="journal article" year="1997">Brescovit 1997</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 151). Here, new illustrations of the well preserved epigynal plate of the Colombian specimen belonging to this species are included.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="6AB59980FFF3FF93FF37FA9CAC2A3C94" pageId="5" pageNumber="586" type="description">
<paragraph id="2210CA0BFFF3FF93FF37FA9CAA7B3DC8" blockId="5.[151,1437,1034,2035]" pageId="5" pageNumber="586">
<emphasis id="10DB1619FFF3FF93FF37FA9CA83D3E79" bold="true" box="[199,345,1322,1348]" pageId="5" pageNumber="586">Description.</emphasis>
<emphasis id="10DB1619FFF3FF93FE91FA9DA8C73E78" box="[353,419,1323,1349]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="586">Male.</emphasis>
(ICN–Ar 9696). Carapace yellowish. Chelicerae brown, labium and endites brown. Sternum reddish-brown. Legs yellow. Abdomen dorsally grayish; ventrally yellow. Spinnerets yellow (
<figureCitation id="BA94D68EFFF3FF93FB04FAF9AC2B3E54" box="[1268,1359,1359,1385]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1872,1896]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,272,1848]" captionTargetId="figure-68@6.[189,1398,272,1848]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3A-H. Mesilla vittiventris Simon, 1903. Male (ICN-Ar 9696):A habitus, dorsal view; C left palp, retroventral view; D palp, retrolateral view; E palp, ventral view; F leg I, ventral view. Female (ICN-Ar 6271): B habitus, dorsal view; G epigynum, ventral view; H epigynum, dorsal view.Abbreviations:A, atrium; CD, copulatory ducts; E, embolus; FD, fertilization ducts; LB, lateral borders; MA, median apophysis; RTA, retrolateral tibial apophysis; S, spermathecae; SD, spermatic ducts; SR, seminal receptacles; T, tegulum. Scale bars: A, B, F: 2mm; C: 1mm; D: 0.5mm; E–H: 0.2mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4506506" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4506506/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="586">Fig. 3A</figureCitation>
). Total length 7.12, carapace length 2.49, width 1.99, high 0.68. Clypeus height 0.15. Eye diameters and interdistances: AME 0.10, ALE 0.18, PME 0.2, PLE 0.21; AME–AME 0.23, AME–ALE 0.35, PME–PME 0.48, PME–PLE 0.38, ALE–PLE 0.43. Chelicerae 1.72 long, distal large retromarginal teeth, six promarginal teeth, six retromarginal denticle Leg I—femur 6.13/ patella 0.86/ tibia 7.08/ metatarsus 6.82/ tarsus 1.87/ total 22.76; II—5.77/ 0.81/ 6.68/ 6.59/ 1.85/ 21.7; III—3.3/ 0.81/ 2.63/ 3.54/ 1.17/ 11.45; IV—4.42/ 0.73/ 4.77/ 6.31/ 1.55/ 17.78. Leg spination (
<figureCitation id="BA94D68EFFF3FF93FA9FF9B5A9DC3D7C" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1872,1896]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,272,1848]" captionTargetId="figure-68@6.[189,1398,272,1848]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3A-H. Mesilla vittiventris Simon, 1903. Male (ICN-Ar 9696):A habitus, dorsal view; C left palp, retroventral view; D palp, retrolateral view; E palp, ventral view; F leg I, ventral view. Female (ICN-Ar 6271): B habitus, dorsal view; G epigynum, ventral view; H epigynum, dorsal view.Abbreviations:A, atrium; CD, copulatory ducts; E, embolus; FD, fertilization ducts; LB, lateral borders; MA, median apophysis; RTA, retrolateral tibial apophysis; S, spermathecae; SD, spermatic ducts; SR, seminal receptacles; T, tegulum. Scale bars: A, B, F: 2mm; C: 1mm; D: 0.5mm; E–H: 0.2mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4506506" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4506506/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="586">Fig. 3F</figureCitation>
): I—II d1-1-0-0-0, v2-2-2-2-2, p0, metatarsus p1-0-0-0-0; III—tibia v0-2-2-0-0, p0-1-1-0-0, r1-1-1-1-0, metatarsus v2-0-0-2-0; IV—tibia v1-1-1-2-1, metatarsus v1-0-1-1-1, p0-2-0-1-2. Abdomen, twice the length of carapace, length 4.61, epigastric furrow 0.68 from tracheal spiracle, spiracle 2.93 from base of spinnerets. Palp: retrolateral tibial apophysis very small, apically sharpened; cymbium shorter than tibia; subtegulum inconspicuous; tegulum longer than wide; median apophysis very long, sinuous and apically inserted; embolus long, basally inserted on the tegulum, apically filiform, with narrow base (
<figureCitation id="BA94D68EFFF3FF93FD65F96DABBF3DC8" box="[661,731,1755,1781]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1872,1896]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,272,1848]" captionTargetId="figure-68@6.[189,1398,272,1848]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3A-H. Mesilla vittiventris Simon, 1903. Male (ICN-Ar 9696):A habitus, dorsal view; C left palp, retroventral view; D palp, retrolateral view; E palp, ventral view; F leg I, ventral view. Female (ICN-Ar 6271): B habitus, dorsal view; G epigynum, ventral view; H epigynum, dorsal view.Abbreviations:A, atrium; CD, copulatory ducts; E, embolus; FD, fertilization ducts; LB, lateral borders; MA, median apophysis; RTA, retrolateral tibial apophysis; S, spermathecae; SD, spermatic ducts; SR, seminal receptacles; T, tegulum. Scale bars: A, B, F: 2mm; C: 1mm; D: 0.5mm; E–H: 0.2mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4506506" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4506506/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="586">Figs 3</figureCitation>
C–E).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2210CA0BFFF3FF93FF37F949AADE3CB8" blockId="5.[151,1437,1034,2035]" pageId="5" pageNumber="586">
<emphasis id="10DB1619FFF3FF93FF37F949A87F3C24" box="[199,283,1791,1817]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="586">Female</emphasis>
. Described by 
<bibRefCitation id="463EB7FAFFF3FF93FE3AF949ABEF3C24" author="Brescovit, A. D." box="[458,651,1791,1817]" pageId="5" pageNumber="586" pagination="1 - 187" refId="ref5286" refString="Brescovit, A. D. (1997) Revisao de Anyphaeninae Bertkau a nivel de generos na regiao neotropical (Araneae, Anyphaenidae). Revista Brasileira de Zoologia, 13, 1 - 187. https: // doi. org / 10.1590 / S 0101 - 81751996000500001" type="journal article" year="1997">Brescovit (1997)</bibRefCitation>
, figs 150-151. 
<emphasis id="10DB1619FFF3FF93FCC9F948ADF03C25" bold="true" box="[825,1172,1790,1816]" pageId="5" pageNumber="586">Complementary description:</emphasis>
Dorsal body as in 
<figureCitation id="BA94D68EFFF3FF93FA80F949A9DF3C00" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1872,1896]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,272,1848]" captionTargetId="figure-68@6.[189,1398,272,1848]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3A-H. Mesilla vittiventris Simon, 1903. Male (ICN-Ar 9696):A habitus, dorsal view; C left palp, retroventral view; D palp, retrolateral view; E palp, ventral view; F leg I, ventral view. Female (ICN-Ar 6271): B habitus, dorsal view; G epigynum, ventral view; H epigynum, dorsal view.Abbreviations:A, atrium; CD, copulatory ducts; E, embolus; FD, fertilization ducts; LB, lateral borders; MA, median apophysis; RTA, retrolateral tibial apophysis; S, spermathecae; SD, spermatic ducts; SR, seminal receptacles; T, tegulum. Scale bars: A, B, F: 2mm; C: 1mm; D: 0.5mm; E–H: 0.2mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4506506" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4506506/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="586">Fig. 3B</figureCitation>
. Epigynum: lateral borders sclerotized, parallel and wide; atrium long; internally with short, wide copulatory ducts; seminal receptacles small and medially situated on the copulatory ducts; spermathecae large, oval, posteriorly positioned; fertilization ducts as long as the spermathecae (
<figureCitation id="BA94D68EFFF3FF93FCDCF8DDAAC93CB8" box="[812,941,1899,1925]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1872,1896]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,272,1848]" captionTargetId="figure-68@6.[189,1398,272,1848]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3A-H. Mesilla vittiventris Simon, 1903. Male (ICN-Ar 9696):A habitus, dorsal view; C left palp, retroventral view; D palp, retrolateral view; E palp, ventral view; F leg I, ventral view. Female (ICN-Ar 6271): B habitus, dorsal view; G epigynum, ventral view; H epigynum, dorsal view.Abbreviations:A, atrium; CD, copulatory ducts; E, embolus; FD, fertilization ducts; LB, lateral borders; MA, median apophysis; RTA, retrolateral tibial apophysis; S, spermathecae; SD, spermatic ducts; SR, seminal receptacles; T, tegulum. Scale bars: A, B, F: 2mm; C: 1mm; D: 0.5mm; E–H: 0.2mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4506506" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4506506/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="586">Figs 3G, H</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2210CA0BFFF3FF93FF37F838AC2A3C94" blockId="5.[151,1437,1034,2035]" box="[199,1358,1934,1961]" pageId="5" pageNumber="586">
<emphasis id="10DB1619FFF3FF93FF37F838A85B3C95" bold="true" box="[199,319,1934,1960]" pageId="5" pageNumber="586">Variation.</emphasis>
Males (n=3): total length: 7.03–8.20; carapace length: 2.05–2.71; femur I length: 6.13–6.66.
</paragraph>
